            <section ID="s27">
               <id root="4443a849-fd78-4d32-b3b7-4a2ed69fd320"/>
               <code code="34076-0" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="INFORMATION FOR PATIENTS SECTION"/>
               <title>17 PATIENT COUNSELING INFORMATION
</title>
               <effectiveTime value="20120206"/>
               <component>
                  <section ID="s28">
                     <id root="7bb5254f-056d-475a-b437-bd84bb944b78"/>
                     <code code="42229-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="SPL UNCLASSIFIED SECTION"/>
                     <title>17.1  Avoiding Contamination of the Product
</title>
                     <text>
                        <paragraph>Patients should be instructed to avoid contaminating the applicator tip with material from the eye, fingers, or other source.
</paragraph>
                     </text>
                     <effectiveTime value="20100520"/>
                  </section>
               </component>
               <component>
                  <section ID="s29">
                     <id root="72a6be88-75e5-46fa-83f6-53614ebda1ae"/>
                     <code code="42229-5" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="SPL UNCLASSIFIED SECTION"/>
                     <title>17.2  Avoidance of Contact Lens Wear
</title>
                     <text>
                        <paragraph>Patients should be advised not to wear contact lenses if they have signs and symptoms of bacterial conjunctivitis.
</paragraph>
